 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Oct. 14: Associated Cement Co?s bottomline swelled by 158.94 per cent at Rs 203.43 crore for the second quarter ended September 30, compared with Rs 78.56 crore a year ago. Total income grew 12.15 per cent at Rs 1,030.22 crore from Rs 918.54 crore last year. ACC today signed an agreement with Everest Finvest (India) for divesting its 50 per cent stake in Everest Industries for Rs 99.16 crore, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange. 

 Mumbai, Oct. 14: SpiceJet Ltd today said it has allotted 61.52 lakh shares of Rs 10 each at a price of Rs 89.30 per equity share to Dubai-based Istithmar PJSC on a preferential basis.

 Mumbai, Oct. 14: Reliance Industries will hold a board meeting on October 27 to consider the un-audited financial results for the quarter ended September 30.

 New Delhi, Oct. 14: The Oil and Natural Gas Corp is planning to raise loans in the overseas markets to fund its foreign acquisitions. In preparation for this, it has asked Moody?s to do a credit rating.

